We checked: What do the side effects after the corona vaccine say?
Many people who get vaccinated feel weak, feverish and tired after receiving the shot, while others do not •
Could this indicate a stronger immune system of those who do experience these symptoms, or is this a baseless rumor?
While more and more people are getting vaccinated, the lack of information about the side effects continues to confuse and create rumors, most of which are not true.
Are the immune systems of those who developed side effects stronger than those whose bodies reacted less severely to the vaccine, which may prove that their systems are unable to fight a foreign body entering the body?
"There are several levels of reactions to the vaccine," says Dr. David Dvir, head of the primary medicine department at Moheded and a member of the advisory committee for the Epidemic Treatment Team, and reassures: "Headaches, fatigue, local pain, these are the immediate reactions of the immune system .
This is how the body reacts to the entry of a foreign body into the system."
Is there a connection between the levels of antibodies that are developed and the side effects?
"There is no correlation between the feelings and the development of antibodies against the virus.
About 50-60% feel the side effects, but about 90% develop protection against the virus.
It was not found that people who developed strong reactions were more protected."
"In the medical literature, there is no correlation between an immediate reaction and the level of the vaccine.
In some trials where people also received placebo vaccines, about a quarter of them developed headaches.
This is also a mental component - how the person perceives the vaccine, if he expects there to be side effects.
Many of the phenomena that happen could also happen normally, but since the public is vaccinated, they attribute the reaction to the vaccine itself, and this is a bias that you see regarding vaccines in general - the attribution of phenomena that happen near the vaccine and are attributed to it."
According to Dr. Dvir, the reasons for the commonly reported symptoms, such as weakness and headaches, are not yet known.
Regarding myocarditis, opinions differ.
"There are all kinds of theories on the subject, but it should be noted that the virus itself causes higher rates of myocarditis than the vaccine.
One of the theories is that it is a strong reaction of the immune system."
Is it even possible to assess the strength of the immune system?
"When students were exposed to the flu virus, they showed that those who didn't sleep or were under higher stress were more vulnerable to infection.
Apart from this, there are laboratory parameters that test the immune system or its components.
When there is a decrease in the immune system, you see it immediately.
People catch many viral or infectious diseases.
It's not like someone walks around with a weak immune system and isn't aware of it.
These are people who come for inquiries because of repeated incidents of infectious diseases, and what affects the system are banal things: stress, nutrition, sleep.
By the way, we also don't want an immune system that is too strong, because it can cause autoimmune diseases."
Soon MRNA vaccines will appear in additional contexts, thanks to the extensive knowledge that has been accumulated about them in recent times.
"There is no doubt that an opening will be paved for other vaccines of this type.
This technology is being tested for many uses beyond vaccines - for the treatment of oncological diseases, for example.
Their efficiency is that the substance stays in the body for a very short time - enters, does its action, and then breaks down.
This technology is not new, but it received a serious boost following the very great need for a rapid vaccine.
Now, for example, we know that an interval of three weeks between doses is too small, and some vaccine experts claim that it is possible that after the third dose we will not need another vaccine in the near term, so it is not clear whether we are going to a situation of vaccination every six months or that the third dose will give an interval bigger".
